<bug>
    <id>46442</id>
    <title>Semicolon in allow/deny all rules cause reverse lookups</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Created attachment 23058
httpd.conf file to cause reverse dns lookups</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">A trailing semicolon in an allow all or deny all rule causes a reverse DNS lookup.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">Since semicolons, per rfc-952, are used to denote comments in the DNS I think httpd should throw an error condition if it encounters a semicolon in a location where it expects a hostname.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
